    <title ixia_locid="1">Configuring Provider Networks Using the CLI</title>
    <shortdesc ixia_locid="2">You can set up provider networks over physical networks using the
            <nameliteral ixia_locid="3">controller-0</nameliteral> command-line interface. The provider networks
        provide connectivity for tenant networks.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author ixia_locid="4">Jim Owens</author>
        <author ixia_locid="5">Tom Towle</author>
        <author ixia_locid="6">Pedro Sanchez</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context id="context_N1002B_N10028_N10001" ixia_locid="7">
            <p ixia_locid="8">You must configure at least one provider network in order to assign
                data interfaces to compute nodes and unlock the hosts. </p>
        </context>
        <!-- Commenting out conref because it points to Sample Installation and Configuration doc <context conref="jow1424191621914.xml#jow1424191621914/note_for_RDS_setup" id="context_N1003C_N1002E_N10001" ixia_locid="13"/> -->
        <prereq id="prereq_N1003C_N10028_N10001" ixia_locid="11">
            <p conref="jow1404333506062.xml#jow1404333506062/prereq-controller-0-ready" ixia_locid="12"/>
        </prereq>
        <context conref="jow1423853504951.xml#jow1423853504951/context_N1003B_N10037_N1000F_N10001" id="context_N1004C_N1002E_N10001" ixia_locid="14"/>
        <context id="context_N10053_N1002E_N10001" ixia_locid="417">
            <p ixia_locid="412">For example, to add a VLAN provider network named providernet-a:</p>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="413"><systemoutput ixia_locid="414">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="415">neutron providernet-create providernet-a --type=vlan</userinput>
<systemoutput ixia_locid="416">Created a new providernet:
